8 1, 2026]: Sec. 7. (a) As used in this section, "sweepstakes game"
9 means a game, contest, or promotion that:
10 (1) is available on the Internet;
11 (2) is accessible on a mobile phone, computer terminal, or
12 similar access device;
13 (3) utilizes a dual-currency or multi-currency system of
14 payment allowing a player to exchange currency for:
15 (A) a cash prize, a cash award, or cash equivalents; or
16 (B) a chance to win a cash prize, a cash award, or cash
17 equivalents; and
18 (4) simulates:
19 (A) lottery games; or
20 (B) casino-style gaming, including slot machines, video
21 poker, table games, bingo, or sports wagering.
22 However, the term does not include a game, contest, or promotion
23 offered by the state lottery commission.
24 (b) The commission may levy a civil penalty in the amount of
25 one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) against an operator or
26 individual who knowingly uses the Internet to conduct a
27 sweepstakes game:
28 (1) in Indiana; or
29 (2) in a transaction directly involving a person located in
30 Indiana.
